# Example environment variables for local development and deployment.
# Copy this file to .env (which should remain gitignored) and fill in real values.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
VITE_TICKETMASTER_API_KEY=your_ticketmaster_key_here
VITE_GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=your_google_places_api_key_here

# Notes:
# - Do NOT commit a real .env file containing secrets.
# - For production, set these variables in your hosting provider / CI (Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Actions, etc.)
#   so they are available at build time.
# - For local dev, create a .env in the project root (same folder as package.json) and restart the dev server.
